aa(lp176
VI used to be a professor teaching about this.
p177
aVNow I'm an activist, a human rights activist,
p178
aVand what drives me is my shame
p179
aVat living in an otherwise great nation
p180
aVthat has less than five percent of the world's population
p181
aVbut almost 25 percent of the world's incarcerated population.
p182
aVIt's the people I meet  who have lost someone
p183
aVthey love to drug-related  violence or prison
p184
aVor overdose or AIDS
p185
aVbecause our drug policies emphasize
p186
aVcriminalization over health.
p187
aVIt's good people who have lost their jobs,
p188
aVtheir homes, their freedom,  even their children
p189
aVto the state, not because they hurt anyone
p190
aVbut solely because they chose to use one drug
p191
aVinstead of another.
