aVWhich is why putting criminal laws and police
p220
aVfront and center in trying to control
p221
aVa dynamic global commodities market
p222
aVis a recipe for disaster.
p223
aVAnd what we really need to do
p224
aVis to bring the underground drug markets
p225
aVas much as possible aboveground
p226
aVand regulate them as  intelligently as we can
p227
aVto minimize both the harms of drugs
p228
aVand the harms of prohibitionist policies.
p229
aa(lp230
VNow, with marijuana, that obviously means
p231
aVlegally regulating and  taxing it like alcohol.
p232
aVThe benefits of doing so are enormous, the risks minimal.
p233
aVWill more people use marijuana?
p234
aVMaybe, but it's not  going to be young people,
p235
aVbecause it's not going to  be legalized for them,
p236
aVand quite frankly, they already have
p237
aVthe best access to marijuana.
p238
aVI think it's going to be older people.
p239
aVIt's going to be people in their 40s and 60s
p240
aVand 80s who find they prefer a little marijuana
p241
aVto that drink in the evening or the sleeping pill
p242
aVor that it helps with  their arthritis or diabetes
p243
aVor maybe helps spice up a  long-term marriage. (Laughter)
