aVLook here in Brazil, and some other countries,
p267
aVwhere a remarkable psychoactive substance,
p268
aVayahuasca, can be legally  bought and consumed
p269
aVprovided it's done so  within a religious context.
p270
aVLook in Bolivia and Peru,
p271
aVwhere all sorts of products  made from the coca leaf,
p272
aVthe source of cocaine,
p273
aVare sold legally over the counter
p274
aVwith no apparent harm to people's public health.
p275
aVI mean, don't forget, Coca-Cola had cocaine in it until 1900,
p276
aVand so far as we know was no more addictive
p277
aVthan Coca-Cola is today.
p278
aa(lp279
VConversely, think about cigarettes:
p280
aVNothing can both hook you  and kill you like cigarettes.
p281
aVWhen researchers ask heroin addicts
p282
aVwhat's the toughest drug to  quit, most say cigarettes.
p283
aVYet in my country and many others,
p284
aVhalf of all the people who  were ever addicted
p285
aVto cigarettes have quit
