aa(lp297
VSo the challenges we face today
p298
aVare twofold.
p299
aVThe first is the policy challenge
p300
aVof designing and implementing alternatives
p301
aVto ineffective prohibitionist policies,
p302
aVeven as we need to get  better at regulating
p303
aVand living with the drugs  that are now legal.
p304
aVBut the second challenge is tougher,
p305
aVbecause it's about us.
p306
aVThe obstacles to reform  lie not just out there
p307
aVin the power of the  prison industrial complex
p308
aVor other vested interests  that want to keep things
p309
aVthe way they are,
p310
aVbut within each and every one of us.
p311
aVIt's our fears and our lack of knowledge
p312
aVand imagination that stands  in the way of real reform.
